    "body": "### Problem\n\nWhen opening Neovim with no active buffers and using the Bufdired plugin (similar to Emacs Dired), the application crashes with an error message indicating that it couldn't open the current buffer.\r\n\r\n\r\n![invalid buffer id ](https://github.com/neovim/neovim/assets/33336001/efb23dff-547e-4fd8-a911-19f01bd64363)\r\n\n\n### Steps to reproduce\n\n* Ensure there are no active buffers (empty Neovim session)\r\n* Trigger Bufdired or perform actions that invoke `nvim.api.buf_get_name()`\n\n### Expected behavior\n\nNeovim should handle the absence of a current buffer gracefully without crashing.\n\n### Neovim version (nvim -v)\n\nv0.10.0-dev-304+g84378c4dd\n\n### Vim (not Nvim) behaves the same?\n\nyes\n\n### Operating system/version\n\nWindows 11\n\n### Terminal name/version\n\nWindows Terminal Latest stable version \n\n### $TERM environment variable\n\nxterm-256\n\n### Installation\n\nrepo",
